Cool day.  62 degrees at 1: 45.  Winds 5 mph NE  bright sunny fantastic day.
Bright sunny winds w-northwest 5 mph.  83 degrees.  A great day.  Water actually clearer than last reading.
Calm. 1/3 to 1/2 inch rain the night before.  78 degrees sunny. a great day.
Calm 2 mph winds.  85 degrees.  Hot hazy very humid.  Algae starting- two weeks later than 1998
Lake calm.  Bright day partly cloudy 75 degrees.  Algae bloom starting good now.
Last year this time- lake was turning over.  Green brown tint water. bright sunny high clouds 75 degrees.  5 mph winds little chop- algae level increasing.
Sunny- calm- surface debris- slight algae bloom
Sunny- 75 F- 5 mph wind- .33" rain last night
Partly sunny- 65 F- 1.5" rain 7/29- W wind 5-7 mph
Bright sun- clouds coming- 68 F- 1.66" rain 8/10- clarity dropped- algae increasing @ 8-12' depths
Bright sun- calm- 75 F- lots of rain past week- algae bloom
Partly sunny- 66 F- sparkling water- slight. chop- algae bloom- 2.6" rain 9/4-5
Sunny- 76 F- .75" rain in last 2 days- 5 mph winds- high fishing pressure- weedy
Northwest wind at 5 mph- partly sunny- little algae- weedy- 73 F- water high
Partly sunny- northwest wind at 3-5 mph- algae level increasing- weeds emerging- 70 F- brown tint appearing- lake activity excellent
Partly sunny- 74 F- low humidity- wind 2-3 mph- algae bloom increasing- bug hatch- Panfishing good- great day- 15-20 per sq. ft. muskie
Sunny- low humidity- 80 F- calm- algae blooms increasing- water quality impressive
Partly sunny- 75 F- SW winds at 2 mph- algae blooms- excellent Muskie fishing this last week- very humid- lake turnover behind
Heavy rains over the weekend churned up water- water's edge is full of garbage- fast-food containers.
Fishing is slow- lake use is below normal- a few weeds in shallows- bright- sunny day.
Air temp 65- calm wind- sunny- surface covered with larva skins- good fishing
Partly sunny- air temp 68- WNW wind 3-5 mph- morning air temp 47- algae starting
Mostly sunny- air temp 74- W wind 3-5 mph- algae increasing - going to brown in weeks time
Mostly sunny- air temp 65- calm wind- algae little change- rainfall 2" above normal for last 4 months
Swimmers itch last 2 weeks- cloudy- air temp 72- algae increasing- increased fish catch
Secchi taken between rain showers when sun came out.  Light wind- some pollen on water near shoreline.  Water temp. 67 degrees.
Partly sunny- near 80 degrees- slight breeze- weeds really growing.
78 degrees- partly sunny- slight breeze- good lake activity- algae really taking off.
76 degrees- clear- sunny- algae + plant growth max.  Lake ready to turn over.  Good fishing activity.
5 mph winds- partly cloudy- great day- 74 degrees.  Ice shoreline damage- esp. north shore this spring-my property included 10 cribs placed in lake 1995.
Calm winds- hazy day- 80 degrees- snails about 15 to 20 per sq. ft. in shallow areas.
70 degrees- partly cloudy- 5-10 mph winds- algae starting June roughly 4" below normal rainfall.
85 degrees- clear 5 to 10 mph- winds W-northwest- fantastic day-.5" rain last night-good lake activity.

Fantastic cobalt blue day- winds 5 mph west- 80 degrees- great water quality-picked up a white latex glove- some young lady didn't want to bait her hook bare handed.  I'll bet she's a messy housekeeper.

5 mph west winds- partly cloudy- 74 degrees.  Great day.  Believe the above average august rainfall had a lot to do with water quality-fewer weeds in lake-swimmers itch no problem now as was case in early July.
5 mph wind ( ) - partly cloudy- 78 degrees. Pollen shoreline-dry-we need rain. Lake activity good.
5 mph SW winds- mostly sunny- algae increasing 70%. Lake usage nearly nil for boating + fishing. Loon-closest ( ) .
Bright sunny day- 5 mph south wind- 73 degrees- very few weeds- algae no problem.
Bright sunny day- calm- 64 degrees- algae blooming- water clarity best since 1989- rainy- wet- cool summer.
Mostly sunny-3 to 5 mph northeast winds. 74 degrees- algae levels increasing- great day for all activities. found an excellent deck shoe (my size) in 2.5' water-hope to find it's mate next outing.
Algae beginning- weed growth 2 weeks behind.  Sunny- bright day with wind 3-4 mph.  Southwest wind.  Rain fall 3-4 inches below normal for May and June in our area.  Very little runoff.
65 degrees- south west winds at 5 mph- bright sunny day.  Haven't heard or seen loons for 3 day.  Thank you personal water crafts- half of which are pulling water skiers.
72 degrees- 3-5 mph winds northeast- partly cloudy- fantastic day.  PWC's must go- fishing poor- haven't seen a loon or heard one for 10 days.
Unusual year.  Algae levels and weed growth much behind former years.  65 degrees.  Partly sunny- winds at 3 mph from the west.  Good lake activity.
Sunny- 68 degrees- 3-5 mph winds.  Turn over not far ahead- cool days.
